Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE JUDGE ON RETURN OF THE BENCH WARRANT.

Defendant Par Ra not in court. 
Attorney Michael K. Moran in court for Par Ra. 
Attorney William R. F. Ackell in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for Calendar Call.   DEFENDANT FAILED TO APPEAR. 
Defense counsel advises the court he has no explanation of defendant's non appearance 
 Court ordered Bench Warrant Issued. Remand to Judge and Forfeiture of Cash Bond.

Attorney Michael K. Moran in court.  Stephan Eduard Nolten for William Ackell  appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case calendared for a Bailbond Hearing.  DEFENDANT FAILED TO APPEAR. 
Defense has no explanation for defendants non appearance and  request a calendar call date.  State does not object. 
Court ordered bench warrant issued and STAYED issuance until the next court date.
 Court ordered matter adjourned back to Branch 19.  Calendar call scheduled for September 6, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Par Ra in court with Attorney Michael K. Moran.  Defendant Par Ra in custody.  Gregg Herman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer N. Grap. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Defense to be heard on bail on the next date. Case is adjourned to Branch 19.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for August 10, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  No driving without a valid license.

Defendant Par Ra in court with attorney Ashley Fard appear friend of the court for Attorney Moran.  Defendant Par Ra in custody.  Gregg Herman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kies, Branch 45. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL. 
Pursuant to Chief Judge Directive 22-04, parties are hereby notified that as of July 30, 2022, this case will be assigned to Branch 19, Judge Kori Ashley, in Room 313 of the Safety Building.  This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast: https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 3, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
